<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05037e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05037e">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05037e"> 37(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> it related of a living bishop / so near as France sanctity / almost unequalled</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;The sensation it <font color="green">[Sulpicius&apos; biography of St. Martin]</font> produced in Rome,&rsquo; says a writer, &lsquo;and throughout the Christian world, was incredible. No book was so much read &hellip; and it was everywhere the subject of conversation. For it related of a living bishop so near as France sanctity almost unequalled, and miraculous powers such as were not then possessed by any one &hellip;.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 66</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
